{"ts":"2026-07-21T19:16:03.605Z","author":"codex-jellyfin","op":"learning_add","patch":[{"op":"replace","path":"/metadata/updated_at","value":"2026-07-21T19:16:03.605Z"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/learnings","value":[{"created_at":"2026-07-21T19:16:03.605Z","author":"codex-jellyfin","text":"Current policy scan found two inline type imports and one parameter-property class; no explicit any types or dynamic imports were found in src. Existing ESLint treats no-explicit-any and unused declarations as warnings and disables the any rule in tests, so it is not yet a mandatory gate."}]}],"before_hash":"4f670ae95a3baf295c22c038b6ad06e953e1a580bbfc24b71e2a1f0af99b775c","after_hash":"08cdc2b24b8b7799d45314b52d50fdae034ad4405628e7a48e0199ec9a7823c2","message":"Record initial TypeScript policy scan"}
